    <section id="overview">
      <h2>Year Overview</h2>
      <p>The Rat (<span class="chinese-char">鼠</span>) occupies the Earthly Branch <strong>Zi (子)</strong>, carrying Water energy. In 2026, a <strong>Fire Horse</strong> (Bing Wu, 丙午) year, the Rat faces its direct opposite across the zodiac — the <strong>Zi-Wu clash</strong> (子午沖). This is the most significant astrological event for Rat-born people this year.</p>
      <p>The Zi-Wu clash creates a direct confrontation between Water and Fire, Yin and Yang. In classical BaZi theory, this opposition brings <strong>disruption to existing structures</strong> but also the potential for transformation. Expect changes in environment, routine, or relationships — some chosen, some forced. The Rat's natural intelligence and adaptability are the greatest assets for navigating this volatile year.</p>
      <p>The Heavenly Stem Bing (丙, Yang Fire) represents the brilliant sun — it illuminates hidden problems but can also scorch those unprepared for its intensity. For the Rat, this means issues that have been buried or avoided will surface and demand attention. Confronting them honestly leads to resolution; avoiding them compounds the difficulty.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>The clash energy makes 2026 a year of <strong>professional upheaval</strong> for many Rat-born people. Job changes, transfers, restructurings, or shifts in industry are common themes. While unsettling, these movements often lead to better positions in the medium term — the Rat's talent for spotting opportunity shines during transitional periods.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> requires particular caution. Fire's impulsive energy tempts speculative ventures, but the overcoming cycle (Water controls Fire) means the Rat must work harder than usual to maintain control over volatile situations. Conservative investment strategies outperform aggressive ones this year. Avoid lending large sums to friends or business partners during clash months (June and December).</p>
      <p><strong>Best sectors:</strong> Technology, communications, consulting, and any field requiring quick thinking and adaptability. The Rat's analytical nature combines well with Fire's creative energy in intellectual pursuits.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>The Zi-Wu clash directly affects the <strong>spouse palace</strong> for many Rat-born charts, creating tension in existing partnerships. Communication breakdowns, disagreements over direction, and power struggles are possible themes. Couples who acknowledge the pressure and create space for honest dialogue will strengthen their bond; those who suppress frustrations risk escalation.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Rats</strong> may find the year brings intense but short-lived romantic encounters. Fire energy creates passionate attraction, but sustainable relationships require the calmer months (March, September, November) to establish foundations. Avoid making permanent commitments during the volatile summer months.</p>
      <p><strong>Family relationships</strong> may also be strained, particularly with older relatives. The Rat's desire for change conflicts with traditional expectations. Patient negotiation yields better results than confrontation.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>The Fire-Water clash manifests physically in the <strong>circulatory and urinary systems</strong> — the organs governed by these elements in Chinese medical theory. Rat-born people should pay attention to heart health, blood pressure, and kidney function during 2026. Regular health check-ups in the first quarter are strongly recommended.</p>
      <p><strong>Mental health</strong> deserves particular attention. The constant friction of clash energy creates underlying anxiety and restlessness. Physical exercise, meditation, and time in nature (especially near water) help restore balance. Swimming and water sports are especially beneficial for Rat-born people this year.</p>
      <p><strong>Travel</strong> is indicated by clash energy — movement and change of environment can be therapeutic. Short trips during favourable months help dissipate accumulated tension.</p>
    </section>

